        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Watch issued June 18 at 8:40PM EDT until June 18 at 10:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WATCH 436 REMAINS VALID UNTIL 10 PM EDT THIS
EVENING FOR THE FOLLOWING AREAS

IN MICHIGAN THIS WATCH INCLUDES 6 COUNTIES

IN SOUTHEAST MICHIGAN

LAPEER                MACOMB                MONROE
OAKLAND               ST. CLAIR             WAYNE

THIS INCLUDES THE CITIES OF ALMONT, CANTON, DEARBORN, FERNDALE,
IMLAY CITY, LAMBERTVILLE, LAPEER, LINCOLN PARK, LIVONIA,
MARYSVILLE, MONROE, NOVI, PONTIAC, PORT HURON, REDFORD,
ROYAL OAK, SOUTHFIELD, ST. CLAIR SHORES, STERLING HEIGHTS,
TAYLOR, TEMPERANCE, TROY, WARREN, WATERFORD, AND WESTLAND.
</description>
